            <title>[FLINK-13589] DelimitedInputFormat index error on multi-byte delimiters with whole file input splits</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-13589</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The DelimitedInputFormat can drops bytes when using input splits that have a length of -1 (for reading the whole file).&#160; It looks like this is a simple bug in handing the delimiter on buffer boundaries where the logic is inconsistent for different split types.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Attached is a possible patch with fix and test.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
